{
  "doc_id": "59559",
  "text": "Another important finding of the present investigation was that RA activated signaling pathways involved in pathologic cardiac remodeling. Several pathways that promote cell growth converge to the activation of mammalian target of rapamycin (mTOR) [CITATION_1] . In fact, mTOR/S6K seems to be involved in pathologic remodeling [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] and mTOR/ PI3K/Akt seem to have a protective role [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] . Cardiac hypertrophy may be associated with the activation of other factors, including members of MAPKs [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] , mainly associated with a pathologic pathway [CITATION_12] [CITATION_13] . Our results showed the non-participation of complex mTOR and PI3K/Akt pathway in the heart supplemented by RA, suggesting that the remodeling process induced by RA has the characteristics observed in cases of pathologic cardiac hypertrophy.",
